
[1]reasonableness

   RE'ASONABLENESS, n.

   1. The faculty of reason. [In this sense, little used.]

   2. Agreeableness to reason; that state or quality of a thing which
   reason supports or justifies; as the reasonableness of our wishes,
   demands or expectations.

   the reasonableness and excellency of charity.

   3. Conformity to rational principles.

   The whole frame and contexture of a watch carries in it a
   reasonableness - the passive impression of the reason or intellectual
   idea that was in the artist. [Unusual.]

   4. Moderation; as the reasonableness of a demand.
